Abdulqadir Ojo, President Moahz Group has promised better services to the Group’s clientele this year. This is as he acknowledged their support in the outgone year and attributed the Group’s success to their patronage. Ojo made the declaration in his New Year message on Sunday. He said, “We, at Moahz Group of companies wish to express our profound gratitude to our esteemed customers and clients for their support and patronage in the year 2021. We do not take it for granted. “We must put it on record that we recorded tremendous success in all our endeavours in the year 2021 which is largely due to your support, love, patronage and referrals.” Ojo added that “As we sojourn through the new year, we pray and hope for a better and continuous harmonious relationship as we promise on our honour to serve you even better.  We wish for a prosperous 2022.” Moahz Group of Companies is a fusion of Moahz Oil and Gas LTD, Moahz Engineering & Project Management LTD, Moahz Investment Limited, Green-Mozaq Classic Limited, and Moahz Multi-Purpose Limited. In 2020, the Group was recognised by the European Business Assembly (EBA), with an award as the best oil and gas installation and service company in West Africa. YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE HEADLINES FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE Lagos Is Second Least Liveable City In The World For 2021 Lagos is the second least liveable city in the world for the year 2021. This is according to the most recent annual ranking put together by the Economist Intelligence Unit (EIU)… FACT CHECK: Did UNICEF Say Blocking Children’s Access To Pornography Constitutes Human Rights’ Infringement? CLAIM 1: A Twitter user claims UNICEF said any efforts to block children from accessing pornography might infringe their human rights. VERDICT: MISLEADING!